    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sets for playing a traditional two-player strategy board game played in Southeast Asia, with the objective to capture more seeds than the opponent. The board is generally long with two rows of seven holes and a larger hole at each end. The seeds can come in the form of pebbles, beans, shells and rubber tree seeds amongst others. This game is known by different names in different cultures and details may vary.</Note_Text>
